<br>
My guild is currently camping RF in sky fire, we've gotten some pretty nasty attitudes from one guild in particular, saying they will KS him. I want opinions from more then one guild on this. RF is an epic mob, and has always been respected as a camp. Is this different now because he's moved to SF? <br>
<br>
I believe he has spawned 6 + times so far since the patch to move him to SF, was he camped by a cleric who's guild later took him down? I don't want to know the in the eyes of Verant crap, because honestly in Verant's eyes there isn't even a camp in a dungeon. King group in os could be petitioned (by an asshole of course) and the guide would have no choice but to share the spawn. Granted this may happen occasionally with jerks, but as a server in general that's not kosher.<br>
<br>
Any opinions? And why? I don't want to spend a week and a half camping him and spend a ton on my phone bill if he pops at 2 am and he will just be ks'd.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukhamelleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khamelleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:03:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> I dont' have much experience in the matter, but intuitively I think people should respect (and hopefully as a community help out if possible) the person/guild who was sitting and waiting for the spawn for days and days rather than try to KS it.  But that's just my opinion.<br>
<br>
I'd be pretty mad if I camped RageFire for days and then excited guildies /shouted &quot;yay RageFire&quot; and then other guilds got wind of it and, however well organized, popped up out of the blue and KSed it in front of me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unosfy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nosfy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:10:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> Common curtesy is that RF is a camp if the cleric is there and calling camp. <br>
<br>
Though, when RF pop, there is a non-said limit of time to kill him. You have to gather fast and kill him. If you take (hypothetical time) 5 hours to gather, I can see a guild willing to take the spawn. Not that I approve that, but I could understand.<br>
<br>
Nosfy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udraelyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draelyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:14:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Is RF a camp or FFA! Need some advice</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately, &quot;in the eyes of verant&quot;, is sometimes the important issue despite how we who get stuck camping the mob, make the rules we do. If Verant thinks something is ffa, and we treat it as ffa, someone who is camping it and gets ks'd is less likely to be the one voted for, if a gm gets involved. <br>
<br>
That being said, I am voting for ffa, in all honesty. I personally have not gotten my epic yet either, so I realize that that means that I could possibly get ks'd. I think, however, that we as the clerics, could set up some form of courtesy rules to abide by, but as I said somewhere else, NO ONE should be forced to waste 6 days of their life camping a spot on the ground, only to have it gangked out from under them. So I propose this:<br>
<br>
First team there with the force to kill him, gets him. None of this kiting around until your team arrives, while another team stands there waiting, crap. If you do have the first team there with enough people to make a VALID attempt, you will be given the space to make the attempt. Since as far as I know, 18 56-60s seems to be around the minimum you can do a kunark dragon with. So perhaps we set that as a precedent? None of this stacking the zone with 40s either because thats not a *valid* force.  If you wipe, and are not the only team waiting that particular spawn, it moves on to the next team. There should be no reason why RF depops because of 1 team wiping, no one wins. However if there is more than 1 team waiting after the first team wipes, how about a /ran 100 between the two ranking officers from each team? It obviously is the fairest, since because of the wipe, both teams had more than enough time to gather recruits, so by then, both probably have a valid force. Not to mention, that were a gm to get involved, they would do the exact same thing, they'd simply random it between the groups. <br>
<br>
Feedback would be preferable, flame if you want, though whether I take it with a grain of salt is wishful thinking<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  As a cleric without his epic, I'd be more than willing to adopt a cycle of this form. No one should honestly be ks'd of something they sat 6 days for, but no person in their right mind should be forced to sit a camp this long, then have to be barraged with tells of how they're going to be ks'd either.<br>
<br>
Draelyn Hammerstone<br>
High priest of Divine grace <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 360<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:14:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> I think that Ragefire will eventually become an FFA mob.  The only thing that is going to make people continue to respect the camp is reputation and peer pressure.  You need to post the name of the guild that is saying that they will KS it, and the name of the person who has been talking to you.  If you don't have the guts to post it, and they KS you, it's your own damned fault.<br>
