Foof <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujaedengrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaeden Grae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 883<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:39:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> Ragefire on our server is and has always been a camp, with the unwritten rules of:<br>
<br>
1.  The cleric's character must be there, actively camping it, responding to camp checks.<br>
2.  There is a limit on how long after he pops you have to gather your forces and kill him.<br>
<br>
It has worked well on our server and we avoid many of the problems other servers have in regard to him.  <br>
<br>
I think it is common courtesy to follow those rules, and those who don't are just being selfish.  And there is no reason to bring Verant's rules into this because VI has a solid rule, there are no camps.  It comes down to us as a server acting like grown-ups and thinking of other people, rather than ourselves.  This, I'm sorry to say, is in short supply these days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 7:42:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> Anam Kara?  That really surprises me.  I bet they back down when word gets back to their officers that one of their clerics is doing this. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>
