<br>
 Saying that &quot;in the eyes of Verant&quot; it isn't a camp really doesn't mean anything. We play the game, and most people respsect others. People probably don't think of this, but everytime you call &quot;mill camped&quot;, or &quot;bat one&quot; or &quot;pit one&quot; (symbolizing a range of levels at which you might camp something) you are taking a chance that the people you are telling are not arse holes who will call a GM. IN the situation I described above in HHP, the guides told us and we wouldn't believe it so a GM came and finally it was the sever GM who came and said that if we don't have logs of him on another character making threats, then there is nothing for us to do but share the camp. He then proceded to sit there to make sure we were giving this guy who got no exp a fair share fo the gobbos down there. So to me &quot;in the eyes of Verant&quot; or &quot;verant meant for...&quot; are not valid aguments.<br>
<br>
