<br>
 If clerics and the people of E-marr decided to make it FFA, then I would hope it didnt just turn into ugly chaos. Maybe the first guild with 3 full groups including a cleric who needs it in the zone gets to make an attempt, as long as it is whitin 30 minutes. It might be possible for really together small guilds with allies, like VP/CBA, to manage to get a force there in time.  <br>
<br>
 I don't really care which way that it goes, both ways have valid reasons. But what I don't want to see is 2 or 3 (or 4 or 6) high-end guilds decide because of &quot;in the eyes of Verant&quot; or any other reason, that RF is now FFA. That means if a cleric HAS been sitting there for days they can take RF anyway. In MY eyes, and perhaps no one else's, if a cleric has arranged their schedule and stayed up all night and sat there through thick and thin, they at least deserve a chance to take it. Not all clerics whit thier epic are computer geeks who don't work and just sit at the comp all the time. Fend for instance works and I have no idea how she managed to get off work to do this camp, but I know that it will proabably we awhile before she can do it again... <br>
<br>
 So in closing, as long as everyone respects each other, each way can work. But people must understand that there is not a way (that i know of) to tell and take a vote with all of E-marr to decide it, so that there won't be anyone there camping it. I feel it would be unjust to force E-marr to go FFA by a few guilds taking some spawns from under the noses of clerics who have been camping them and saying &quot;FFA&quot;. <br>
